        public HttpPipeline​(HttpClient httpClient,
                    HttpPipelineOptions requestPolicyOptions,
                    HttpPipelinePolicy... pipelinePolicies)
        Creates a HttpPipeline holding array of policies that gets applied to all request initiated through send(HttpPipelineCallContext) and it's response.
        Parameters:
        httpClient - the http client to write request to wire and receive response from wire.
        requestPolicyOptions - optional properties that gets available in HttpPipelineCallContext for policies.
        pipelinePolicies - pipeline policies in the order they need to applied

      • HttpPipeline

        public HttpPipeline​(HttpPipelineOptions requestPolicyOptions,
                    HttpPipelinePolicy... pipelinePolicies)
        Creates a HttpPipeline holding array of policies that gets applied all request initiated through send(HttpPipelineCallContext) and it's response. The default HttpClient HttpClient.createDefault() will be used to write request to wire and receive response from wire.
        Parameters:
        requestPolicyOptions - optional properties that gets available in HttpPipelineCallContext for policies.
        pipelinePolicies - pipeline policies in the order they need to applied
